data.enText: a person or thing that is unusual and is therefore often valuable or interesting

data.chText: 在商界位居高职的妇女仍然十分罕见。
data.enText: Women are still something of a rarity in senior positions in business.

data.chText: 他收藏的植物包括许多稀有品种。
data.enText: His collection of plants contains many rarities.

data.chText: 古董的价值依它们的保存状况和稀有程度而定。
data.enText: The value of antiques will depend on their condition and rarity.

tr: something unusual -- perhaps worthy of collecting

example: the tenuity of the upper atmosphere

value.def: If someone or something is a rarity, they are interesting or valuable because they are so unusual.

example.ex: Motorized wheelchairs are a rarity here...
example.tran: 电动轮椅在这里很罕见。

example.ex: He was a rarity among Wall Street lawyers...
example.tran: 他在华尔街的律师当中是个奇人。

example.ex: Sontag has always been that rarity, a glamorous intellectual...
example.tran: 桑塔格一直是那种兼具美貌与智慧的人中龙凤。

example.ex: Other rarities include an interview with Presley.
example.tran: 其他的稀罕事包括对普雷斯利的采访。

value.tran: 罕见的人（或物）；奇物;珍品

value.def: The rarity of something is the fact that it is very uncommon.

example.ex: This indicates the rarity of such attacks...
example.tran: 这显示出这种疾病发作的罕见性。

example.ex: It was a real prize due to its rarity and good condition...
example.tran: 因为稀有并且品相完好，它价值连城。

example.ex: 'Its rarity value is high,' Gibson announced gravely.
example.tran: “它极为稀罕，”吉布森严肃地宣布。
